quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  2,199,"Then depart from the place from where [all] the people depart and ask forgiveness of Allāh. Indeed, Allāh is Forgiving and Merciful."
  2,200,"And when you have completed your rites, remember Allāh like your [previous] remembrance of your fathers or with [much] greater remembrance. And among the people is he who says, "
  2,201,"But among them is he who says, "
  3,139,"So do not weaken and do not grieve, and you will be superior if you are [true] believers."
  3,140,"If a wound should touch you - there has already touched the [opposing] people a wound similar to it. And these days [of varying conditions] We alternate among the people so that Allāh may make evident those who believe and [may] take to Himself from among you martyrs - and Allāh does not like the wrongdoers -"
  3,141,"And that Allāh may purify the believers [through trials] and destroy the disbelievers."
  4,79,"What comes to you of good is from Allāh, but what comes to you of evil, [O man], is from yourself.{1} And We have sent you, [O Muḥammad], to the people as a messenger, and sufficient is Allāh as Witness.{2}",footnotes:1:[As a result of],footnotes:2:[your mistakes or sins.]
  4,80,"He who obeys the Messenger has obeyed Allāh; but those who turn away - We have not sent you over them as a guardian."
  4,81,"And they say, "
  5,16,"By which Allāh guides those who pursue His pleasure to the ways of peace{1} and brings them out from darknesses into the light, by His permission, and guides them to a straight path.",footnotes:1:i.e., security, well-being, integrity and escape from Hellfire.  Literally, "freedom from all evil."
  5,17,"They have certainly disbelieved who say that Allāh is Christ, the son of Mary. Say, "
  5,18,"But the Jews and the Christians say, "
